      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CHARLOTTING (7) in career best form and had excuses when she struggled to run the 2200m out at Dubbo. Backs-up quickly and assess on the two sharp earlier wins. Maps well and can return winning form today. THE BENTLEY (6) starting to hit his straps as he gets out in trip. Looks up to this much tougher contest after shouldering the 60kg with a game win over 1600m at Walgett. Can sit off the good tempo and close strongly. EGYPTOLOGIST (4) proved too strong at Hawkesbury two runs back over the 1800m, them up in the weights when slow into stride with a disappointing eleventh over 1600m at Warren. Undefeated over this track and trip and gets his chance in this race. THE GREAT ARMADA (5) progressing well in easier company and deserves his chance here after coming back in trip for a plugging third over 1400m at Tamworth. Winning apprentice sticks and won over the trip two-back. MARIOTA (9) keep safe from the low gate and can sneak into the minor money.",
